---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research — ACLEDS"
  description="ACLEDS research themes: learning analytics, educational data science, and mathematics education"
>
  <section class="page-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Scholarship</p>
      <h1>Research</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-sub">
        Our work spans three intersecting themes — each grounded in African
        educational contexts and oriented toward generating findings that
        matter.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Learning Analytics -->
  <section class="section" id="learning-analytics">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="research-theme-grid">
        <div class="theme-sidebar">
          <div class="theme-number">01</div>
          <div class="theme-icon-lg">
            <svg
              width="36"
              height="36"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.25"
              ><path d="M3 3v18h18"></path><path d="m19 9-5 5-4-4-3 3"
              ></path></svg
            >
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-body">
          <p class="eyebrow">Theme 01</p>
          <h2>Learning Analytics</h2>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p>
            Learning analytics concerns the measurement, collection, analysis,
            and reporting of data about learners — with the purpose of
            understanding and optimising learning and the environments in which
            it occurs. Our work in this area develops and applies analytical
            approaches suited to African school contexts, where data
            infrastructure and availability differ substantially from
            high-income settings.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top:1rem">
            We are particularly interested in how learning analytics can surface
            patterns in engagement, achievement, and learning trajectory that
            are invisible to teachers and school administrators working with
            traditional assessment data alone.
          </p>
          <div class="theme-questions">
            <h4>Key Questions</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>
                How can learning analytics be implemented ethically and
                effectively in under-resourced school settings?
              </li>
              <li>
                What data sources are available and appropriate in African
                contexts?
              </li>
              <li>
                How do learning trajectories differ across school types,
                geographies, and learner populations?
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="theme-divider" />

  <!-- Educational Data Science -->
  <section class="section" id="data-science">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="research-theme-grid">
        <div class="theme-sidebar">
          <div class="theme-number">02</div>
          <div class="theme-icon-lg">
            <svg
              width="36"
              height="36"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.25"
              ><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"></circle><path
                d="M12 2v3M12 19v3M4.22 4.22l2.12 2.12M17.66 17.66l2.12 2.12M2 12h3M19 12h3M4.22 19.78l2.12-2.12M17.66 6.34l2.12-2.12"
              ></path></svg
            >
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-body">
          <p class="eyebrow">Theme 02</p>
          <h2>Educational Data Science</h2>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p>
            Educational data science applies computational and statistical
            methods to education data at scale — to surface patterns, test
            hypotheses, and generate models that can inform teaching and policy.
            Our work in this theme focuses on developing methodological
            approaches appropriate to the data environments typical of African
            education systems.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top:1rem">
            This includes work on data cleaning and curation, missing data
            handling in longitudinal studies, predictive modelling of
            achievement, and the responsible use of algorithmic tools in
            education contexts.
          </p>
          <div class="theme-questions">
            <h4>Key Questions</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>
                What statistical and machine learning approaches are valid for
                African educational datasets?
              </li>
              <li>
                How can education data be collected and managed in ways that
                protect student privacy?
              </li>
              <li>
                What can administrative data reveal about systemic patterns in
                learning outcomes?
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="theme-divider" />

  <!-- Mathematics Education -->
  <section class="section" id="mathematics">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="research-theme-grid">
        <div class="theme-sidebar">
          <div class="theme-number">03</div>
          <div class="theme-icon-lg">
            <svg
              width="36"
              height="36"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.25"
              ><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"></path><path
                d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"
              ></path></svg
            >
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-body">
          <p class="eyebrow">Theme 03</p>
          <h2>Mathematics Education</h2>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p>
            Mathematics education is a central concern for African educational
            systems, where mathematics outcomes at the primary and secondary
            level have significant downstream consequences for access to higher
            education, STEM pathways, and economic participation. Our work
            investigates how mathematics confidence, identity, and achievement
            develop over time — and what factors predict trajectories of success
            or disengagement.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top:1rem">
            This theme connects directly to our flagship study, the Longitudinal
            Mathematics Learning Analytics Study (LMLAS), which tracks cohorts
            of learners over multiple years using both quantitative and
            qualitative data.
          </p>
          <div class="theme-questions">
            <h4>Key Questions</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>
                How does mathematics confidence develop (or erode) across
                primary schooling?
              </li>
              <li>
                What is the relationship between mathematical identity and
                measurable achievement?
              </li>
              <li>
                Which pedagogical and environmental factors predict positive
                mathematics trajectories?
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <a
            href="/projects/lmlas"
            class="btn btn-dark btn-sm"
            style="margin-top:1.5rem">View Flagship Study →</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section section-fog">
    <div
      class="container"
      style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:2rem"
    >
      <div>
        <h2>See the Work in Practice</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:0.5rem">
          Browse active projects and published outputs from our research
          programme.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex; gap:1rem; flex-wrap:wrap">
        <a href="/projects" class="btn btn-dark">Projects</a>
        <a href="/publications" class="btn btn-primary">Publications</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 6rem 0 5rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .page-hero-sub {
    color: rgba(232, 237, 244, 0.7);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 58ch;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .research-theme-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .theme-sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .theme-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    color: var(--fog);
    line-height: 1;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .theme-icon-lg {
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .theme-body h2 {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .theme-body p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .theme-questions {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--fog);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .theme-questions h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .theme-questions ul {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .theme-questions li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .theme-questions li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 4px;
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--gold);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .theme-divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--fog);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .research-theme-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }
    .theme-sidebar {
      flex-direction: row;
      justify-content: flex-start;
    }
    .theme-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
